# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version.
#   Document it in README.md instead.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, if you're executing scripts in a custom environment or QGIS, you might ignore it.
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipenv, see https://python-poetry.org/docs/basic-usage/#commit-your-poetrylock-to-version-control
# poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipenv and Poetry, PDM lockfile must be committed.
# .pdm-python.json
# pdm.lock

